        "ask_llm2": {
            "node": {
                "enum_node_value": "ask_llm",
                "name": "ask_llm2",
                "output_variables_key": [
                    "review_report"
                ],
                "next_nodes_number": 1,
                "list_next_node_key": [
                    "python_code_executor1"
                ],
                "parent_key": "iteration",
                "llm_api_key": "deepseek-chat",
                "list_llm_api_key": null,
                "is_multiple_llm": false,
                "system_prompt": "",
                "system_prompt_variable_key": null,
                "system_prompt_filename": null,
                "system_prompt_source_value": "scroll_text_editor",
                "user_prompt": "Below is the general guide:\n$general_guide\n\nBelow is the job instructions:\n$job_instructions\n\nBelow is the history of terminal commands, your questions and user input:\n$history\n\nDo not waste time on meaningless repeating of terminal commands.\n\nBelow is the check item you prepared earlier:\n$check_item\n\nBelow is the terminal commands you prepared to inspect/diagnose the server.\n$list_terminal_commands\n\nThe terminal output might be too long and will be showed the last.\n\nPlease review the terminal output to determine whether the job is done or the next steps to take.\nThe next steps include:\n1. Ask user to provide inputs or confirmation. Put your question or decription in \"question\".\n2. Further terminal commands. Put them in \"list_terminal_commands\".\n3. If the job is done, put a brief conclusion in \"conclusion\".\n\nThe format is:\n{\"review_report\":\n { \n  \"status\": \"done/ask_user_input/further_commands\",\n  \"list_terminal_commands\": [....],\n  \"question\":\"...\",\n  \"conclusion\": \"...\"\n }\n}\n\n\nThe terminal output is:\n$terminal_output",
                "user_prompt_variable_key": null,
                "user_prompt_filename": null,
